00:00:00.500 --> 00:00:03.790
We're honoring Nicholas Xiarhos
as a team coming out here.

00:00:09.820 --> 00:00:12.830
We wanted to do a Tough Mudder
because it's in honor of Nick.

00:00:12.830 --> 00:00:15.980
But it's really just in honor
of everyone-- came back,

00:00:15.980 --> 00:00:18.020
didn't come back, just
veterans in general.

00:00:21.570 --> 00:00:24.600
Being a vet, being a vet,
being a bet, not being a vet,

00:00:24.600 --> 00:00:28.530
but we're just big supporters of combat
vets coming back and needing help.

00:00:28.530 --> 00:00:30.599
And this type of event helps us.

00:00:30.599 --> 00:00:33.390
It's the camaraderie that you lose
when you get out that comes back

00:00:33.390 --> 00:00:35.026
when you do these type of events.

00:00:37.870 --> 00:00:41.660
So Carry the Fallen is an organization
that helps veterans coming back

00:00:41.660 --> 00:00:43.340
suffering from post-traumatic stress.

00:00:43.340 --> 00:00:44.910
People need to know about it.

00:00:44.910 --> 00:00:48.380
So today, I must've talked
to 25 people, informing them

00:00:48.380 --> 00:00:52.880
what we do as a team to raise money
and awareness for veteran suicide.

00:00:52.880 --> 00:00:58.290
We're carrying those that can't do
this with us, so we added 30 pounds.

00:00:58.290 --> 00:01:00.610
So we named it Nick in honor of Nick.

00:01:00.610 --> 00:01:02.640
In his memory, carrying
the rock along with us,

00:01:02.640 --> 00:01:04.306
so we're doing it for those that can't.

